message.content:
Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper discusses the adaptation of Rissanen's Minimum Description Length (MDL) principle to handle continuous attributes in the Inductive Logic Programming setting. This involves the creation of rules to handle the continuous attributes. 

Probabilistic Methods are present in the text as the MDL pruning mechanism developed in the paper involves calculating the probability of a model given the data and the model complexity. This probability is used to determine which models to prune, with the goal of producing more comprehensible models while retaining their performance.
